@ok The problem is that you are assuming that cLUT and shaper/matrix tags are interchangeable, and if both are present, that the shaper/matrix is there to allow greater performance.

In my experience in creating and using ICC profiles, and in the feedback from most users, this is rarely the case. Typically a user will choose between cLUT and shaper/matrix, depending on their accuracy requirements. If they are aware that many Applications/CMMs have different performance characteristics for these profile types, then they will also take this into consideration when making their choice.

Having both sets of tags in a profile is not usual (and is not actually possible if the Profile Connection Space is L*a*b*), and such profiles were only being created by ArgyllCMS as a diagnostic aid. Since this has partly lead to the current issue, I will remove this default behavior, so that the users preferences are unambiguous.

